Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Remove the stalk top from the @aubergine{1}, cut it in half, then cut each half into four long strips. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1} into half moons. Slice each @chestnut mushrooms{150%g} into about four slices. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #colander{}. Peel and chop the @baking potato{1} into small 1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat, add the mushrooms and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. While they are cooking, lay the aubergine slices on a lined #baking tray{} and sprinkle over half the @shawarma seasoning mix{1/2}, a good glug of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Toss to coat (make sure they're in a single layer) and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and soft, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the onion to the frying pan, stir and cook until the onion is soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the remaining @shawarma seasoning mix{1/2}, stir well and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @white wine vinegar{12%ml}. Stir and allow to evaporate.

Pour in the @water{350%ml} and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1/2}, then add the chickpeas and potato. Mix well and bring to a simmer, then cover the frying pan with a #lid{} (or some #foil{}). Turn the heat to medium-low and simmer until the potato is soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir a couple of times.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Meanwhile, chop the @medium tomato{2}(chopped into 2cm chunks). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{10%g} (stalks and all). Roughly chop the @walnuts{25%g}. Squeeze the @lemon{1/2}(juiced) juice into a #bowl{} and add the @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the tomato, parsley and walnuts, stir together and leave to the side.

When the potato is ready, spoon the mixture into #bowls{} and top with the shawarma roasted aubergine. Spoon the nutty tomato salsa on top. Enjoy!